        <section class="segment-opener" data-uuid="1f0e4807edfe451583e02c8df85b7653">
            <article data-uuid="df1912a091f04966a88f74b2c93833a7">
                <h4 data-uuid="a9d4a538166849dcb156c5430bf47836">Main Idea</h4>
                <p class="main-idea" data-uuid="faf7f472b6b5450c8be112353a5f65ea">Despite a difficult beginning, the English colonies soon flourished.</p>
                <h2 data-uuid="88405417381741f99f5ca3dcf6ff7ed6">The English Colonies</h2>
                <div class="yellow-star-yellow-bar" data-uuid="63392cd2ae6245b7b79eeb5a0648dda4"></div>
            </article>
        </section>
        <p data-uuid="114b74ae50b44db688e5b15aaa649fba">The first permanent English settlement in North America was <dfn title="Jamestown">Jamestown</dfn>, in what is now Virginia. In time, England founded thirteen colonies in North America, in three general regions, each with its own unique characteristics.<br />
        </p>
